Class Calendar

public class Calendar
extends com.google.api.client.googleapis.services.GoogleClient

Service definition for Calendar (v3).

Lets you manipulate events and other calendar data.

For more information about this service, see the API Documentation

This service uses JsonHttpRequestInitializer to initialize global parameters via its Calendar.Builder. Sample usage: 

  public class CalendarRequestInitializer implements JsonHttpRequestInitializer {
      public void initialize(JsonHttpRequest request) {
        CalendarRequest calendarRequest = (CalendarRequest)request;
        calendarRequest.setPrettyPrint(true);
        calendarRequest.setKey(ClientCredentials.KEY);
    }
  }

1.3.0
